  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Dangshen comes from a climbing plant native to northeast China. It is a sweet, neural herb associated with the lung and spleen meridians. Its applications include tonifying the chi, strengthening the middle jiao, tonifying the lungs, nourishing blood, restoring the constitution and expelling pathogens. It is commonly used to treat chi deficiency, which is characterised by symptoms such as fatigue, lack of appetite, weakness and diarrhea.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "黨蔘是常用的補氣藥，藥味甘，藥性平和，歸肺、脾經，能補中益氣、補肺生津。常用於中氣不足引起的慢性疲勞綜合症、腸胃欠佳、四肢乏力等等。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "黨参是常用的补气药，药味甘，药性平和，歸肺、脾经，能补中益气、补肺生津。常用于中气不足引起的慢性疲勞綜合症、肠胃欠佳、四肢乏力等等。\n"
  },
  "tcmModernResearch": {
    "en": "Dangshen is an adaptogenic, meaning it has both stimulating and inhibiting effects on the central nervous system. It is also able to treat and prevent peptic ulcers, stimulate the immune system and temporarily lower blood pressure.\n",
